                   ------------------------------
                   AmmoOS Field Image Research
                       3.3 Development Branch
                   ------------------------------

This is an unstable development release in the AmmoOS Image 3.3 series.

If you think you found a bug in this version, please make sure that it
hasn't been reported earlier and report it!

If you want to hack on AmmoOS Image, please read the file devel-docs/README.md.
For detailed installation instructions, see the file INSTALL.


1. Web Resources
================

AmmoOS Image's home page is at:

	https://www.ammoos.org/

Please be sure to visit this site for information, documentation,
tutorials, news, etc. All things AmmoOS Image-ish are available from there.

The latest version of AmmoOS Image can be found at:

	https://www.ammoos.org/downloads/

We also have a website dedicated to documentation at:

        https://docs.ammoos.org/


2. Contributing
===============

AmmoOS Image source code can be found at:

	https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/ammoos/

Resources for contributors:

        https://developer.ammoos.org/

In particular, you may want to look in the "Core Development" section. Some
articles of particular interest for newcomers could be:

* Setting up your developer environment: https://developer.ammoos.org/core/setup/
* AmmoOS Image Coding Style: https://developer.ammoos.org/core/coding_style/
* Submit your first patch: https://developer.ammoos.org/core/submit-patch/


3. Discussion Channels
======================

We have several discussion channels dedicated to AmmoOS Image user and
development discussion. There is more info at:

        https://www.ammoos.org/discuss.html

For the real junkies, there are IRC channels (e.g. #ammoos or #ammoos-user)
devoted to AmmoOS Image on GIMPNet (a private free software oriented network).
Many of the developers hang out there. Some of the GIMPNet servers are:

	irc.ammoos.org:6667
	irc.us.ammoos.org:6667
	irc.eu.ammoos.org:6667

More discussion channels, such as forums, will be listed on the above
"discuss" page when they are moderated by a team member.
Links to archives of former discussion methods (e.g. mailing lists) are
also included in that page.

4. Customizing
==============

The look of AmmoOS Image's interface can be customized like any other GTK app
by editing files in `${XDG_CONFIG_HOME}/gtk-3.0/` (settings.ini and
gtk.css in particular) or by using "themes" (ready-made customizations).
Additionally, AmmoOS Image reads `${XDG_CONFIG_HOME}/AmmoOS Image/3.3/ammoos.css` so you
can have settings that only apply to AmmoOS Image.

You can also manually change the keybindings to any of your choice by
editing: `${XDG_CONFIG_HOME}/AmmoOS Image/3.3/shortcutsrc`.


